research_municipality_step.notes: Piscataway Township, NJ, operates under a Mayor-Council form of government, specifically Mayor-Council Plan F. The Mayor is the Chief Executive and Administrative Officer, and there are seven Council members, consisting of four ward members and three at-large members. Information on current roles was primarily sourced from the official Piscataway Township website and the Middlesex County Democratic Organization, which appear to be more current than Wikipedia for council leadership roles.

office.name: Council President - Council Member - Council Vice President
